You just need access the field via the `module` object! So, if your field’s internal name is `vehicle_manufacturer`, you can make comparisons against the currently selected option like this:
```{% if module.vehicle_manufacturer == "bmw" %}
  // render BMW stuff
{% elif module.vehicle_manufacturer == "Mercedes" %}
  // render Mercedes stuff
{% else %}
  // render generic/all-purpose stuff
{% endif %}```
All of your module’s fields are going to be accessed via that `module` object. Information in that object will be specific to each module instance, so you won’t have to worry about accessing module data from another part of the page.
